      {
        "id": "415c717a633e9263d02506067894ce5ef62cd9fc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 741,
          "name": "Kanagaraj Manickam",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kanagaraj.manickam@huawei.com",
          "username": "mkr1481"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-10 09:19:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(3 comments)",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "fea91d08fa15fb5cb2c458c90e09ad70d0fc9a03",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3405,
          "name": "Christina Monteleone",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "christina.monteleone@att.com",
          "username": "CMonteleone"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-10 12:41:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI agree with Kanagaraj's comments on network-ref and transparent. I'd like more information on what a network-ref is and I'm also not sure that transparent needs to be indexed.\n\nI would prefer to introduce an orchestration-status property on p-interface over using the inv-status property; it probably should have been the former to begin with.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "43efa092bac2c13775b8e33f54f26f64c64f796c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-13 00:55:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOn the meaning of networkRef, I will seek clarification from developers.\n\nOn indexing of transparent, it was a guess that it would help with query filters, but it can be omitted if necessary.\n\nOn inv-status vs operational-status, we don't know the full impact of reusing/renaming an existing status field, since that affects other components, so it seemed prudent to add a new status to retain backwards-compatibility and limit the scope of breaking changes.\n\nAs to the naming of \"orchestration-status\" vs \"operational-status\", please note that \"operational-status\" fields have also been added to several other elements (commits not yet pushed) so that will have impact across the code for several elements.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d75a08c7a1aec5882b67ebd53cb907d6fff8f06f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-13 02:15:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI note that service-instance contains an \"orchestration-status\" property, so I agree it would be good to be consistent with this.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "ef2c498f65380e7b321efc5224cbad60213de0f5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-13 03:18:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI also note that logical-link already contains an \"operational-status\" property. The p-interface change would have been copying this approach.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "353402c77c24e1ca43afaf1797f1c8bd770bd541",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-13 04:22:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nInterestingly, the allotted-resource element already contains both \"orchestration-status\" and \"operational-status\", suggesting that both of these are required.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "0cfadeb13deff0ffffd2100c2131ac4760e19b13",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-13 08:17:28.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nRegarding the \"network-ref\" contents, please refer to the comment in the wiki page: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/AAI-CCVPN+Schema+Proposal+for+Casablanca+Release#comment-38118309\nThe value comes from an \"ietf-restconf-notification\" for a \"termination point\".",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
